                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d735">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/10–245: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eddy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-03T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 3, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>297. Your 372 Oct 2.<note n="56" xml:id="d735fn56">Not printed, but see footnote
                        55, <ref target="#pg_755">p. 755</ref>.</note> Please advise urgently
                    whether our assumption is correct that version of Feb 14 conversation which King
                    desires to publish is memo written by you and subsequently cleared with
                    Roosevelt and King. We also assume King is proposing unilateral rather than
                    joint publication of memo and letter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
